observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

a) Direct the Municipal Treasurer and the Municipal Accountant to	maintain Property Cards and Ledger Cards, respectively; 

b) and direct the Municipal Accountant to submit immediately the Reports on the Physical Count on all PPEs of the LGU and to disclose the total Road Network System in the Notes to the Financial Statements.

From the foregoing violations, we recommended that Management:

a) 	Stop and avoid further payment of the land purchase;

b)	Submit the lacking documentary requirements;

c)	Submit written explanations and/ or justifications on why the violations were committed; and
d)	Ensure that future procurement of land should be in accordance with the IRR of RA 10752 and Section 13.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive:
1. Require the Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) with coordination of the Municipal Engineer to submit at the beginning of the year to the Auditor a list of all on-going government projects/ programs/ activities (“PPA”) and those that are to be implemented during the year as provided for in Section 2.1 of COA Circular No. 2013- 004 dated January 30, 2014. Likewise, maintain and submit a Monthly Monitoring Report on the Project Status every 3rd day of the following month;

2. Direct the BAC Secretariat to submit the contracts/purchase orders and each of all the documents forming part thereof within five (5 working days from its execution to the Auditor pursuant to Section 3.1.1 of COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009. Otherwise, any unjustified failure of the officials and employees concerned to comply with the requirements herein imposed shall be subject to the administrative disciplinary action provided in (a) Section 127 of Presidential Decree No. 1445; (b) Section 55, Title I-B, Book V of the Revised Administrative Code of 1987; and (c) Section 11 of Republic Act No. 6713.

